      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candle flickers so low... just like everything else. To think, that after all the promises whispered under the willow tree, he could cast me aside so coldly. The world feels so heavy, so terribly hollow. I feel as though I am merely a ghost haunting my own life, waiting for the darkness to finally claim what is left of me. Is there any peace to be found, other than in the silence of the night?",
